Article 39 Cost to Abort in Nepal

Abortion is not obtainable or available in Nepal, except in rare and exceptional situations. Medical abortion is the only legal form of abortion in Nepal. Costs for sex determination and abortion costs fluctuate depending on the local, private, or public facility.

Abortion in Nepal is restricted. Almost every kind of abortion is illegal in Nepal, except in cases where it constitutes a direct danger to the life of the pregnant woman, and/or in cases of rape. Late abortions are illegal and punishable by the death penalty.

Additionally, abortion is prohibited even in the case of pregnancy as a result of rape. Abortion is considered a threat to life as well as a danger to the health of a woman. Because the procedure poses such a significant risk to women, woman’s health is the sole deciding factor when requesting whether somebody may have an abortion or not…

Article 92 Legal Indications for Abortions

Before the abortion may be authorized, four conditions must be met:

Certain life-threatening conditions exist

The fetus poses a life-threatening risk to the mother

Rape

Peer or family pressure

Wrong or illegal method in abortion

Article 114: Requirements For An Abortion

In Nepal, abortion is only legal if carried out by a licensed and trained practitioner. Abortion is also only legal if care isn’t available
